Federal government regulations and the American Heart Association have for decades warned that excess salt contributes to the deaths of tens of thousands of Americans each year . 
  Some scientists are now saying that the average American salt consumption rate carries no risk . 
  The Dietary Guidelines for 2015 dictate the people should limit their intake to 2,300 milligrams . 
  The average American eats about 3,500 milligram of salt per day . 
 